latestIgtvVideos.caption: Tonight I put my Otis bear to bed one last time at 11months for him to wake up ONE ..... my heart is officially gone today... 🤍🐻😭 ... sharing a clip into his birth.... my face in complete pain , shock and disbelief because Otis weighed in at 9lb 12 our heaviest baby..... and born within 1 hour on nothing but fresh air. 😭

latestPosts.caption:
Our story…..Today I have partnered with @my1styears who work alongside @blisscharity to support babies that are born sick or prematurely. I share my story and journey with them to help others who have been affected in a similar situation.Our journey as you know was so beautiful until after the birth of our twin boys which resulted in me suffering from sepsis and sadly one of our twins August suffering the effects of it where he was left critical in neonatal. He suffered from respiratory distress syndrome. Whilst our other twin Arhlo continued to thrive , the journey was something I struggled to mentally cope with at the time. Being strong is all I know but this was one of the hardest things we had to go through as a family. I felt broken in a way I have never felt before. I felt alone. Our experience with the neonatal was everything we could imagine it to be. Without the amazing efforts of the staff and consultants who cared for our babies, we know our story could have been very different. We are eternally grateful. That’s why with my 1st years, they donate a percent for every purchase made to @blisscharity. A charity which believes that every single baby that’s born sick or prematurely (which is 1 in 13) has the best chance of survival and quality of life. Bliss are here to provide you with the mental care and support you need after these life experiences. Head over to my1st years to read their blog and our story with them.

What makes me happy - THIS 🎃🍂🥰 my gang …sometimes literally cannot believe I am a mum to 8 children!!! 8!!!! always gotta include my invisible eldest child Owen 😂… he’s 17 and way to cool for us now 😥 . So if we can just mentally visualise him in this 😂 🤎 how are they all mine! I just don’t know 🥹🥹🥹🥹 it’s wild, it’s crazy, it’s chaotic and time is just rushing past now! I wouldn’t have it any other way

.
.
Family of 10….💙💙🙏🏻🙏🏻
5~07~21
Our twin boys Born at 34 weeks…. 
Sharing your sister Nevaeh’s 10th birthday 
Welcome to the world our beautiful boys 
.
It’s been one LONG week…. I can’t even find the words to begin. Our boys born on Nevaeh’s 10th birthday within 50 minutes on arrival to the hospital! We just made it! 🥺….. the most amazing intense natural births I have ever felt …. I couldn’t have wished for more. 🤍
.
.
However The reason behind my silence is I very quickly became poorly after labour to discover an infection of Group B Strep (usually harmless to mums) made its way into my uterus and then extremely rare to enter the bloodstream causing sepsis in me and a wave of panic upon us all…. We all don’t need to be told how fatal this could have been! Our boys escaped it 🙏🏻 but our twin 1 had a bumpy start and felt some of the trauma it caused…. Where he spent a few days on ventilator … and had lots of testing. I will go more in depth on it at some point. I spent the week in hospital only to have got home . My inner strength left me quickly feeling petrified of what could have happened, my mind and body has suffered trauma I just now feel I want to erase. Im on a heavy powerful antibiotic given intravenously for 7 days… I did get let go Saturday evening but will continue the course back and fourth untill Wednesday via out patients. Thanking these beautiful boys for knowing when to get out quickly and safely! Both boys are doing amazing in Neonatal …. But not for long at all….already been told to prepare for their homecoming 🙏🏻… And to Jon…. Words dont even come close to how much I love you and how you carried me through 🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻 . A love beyond compare. A new journey begins. 🤍
